      "text": "One of the [[Fallacious Argument]]s, and a relative of both [[Ad Verecundiam]] (argument by authority) and [[Idont Suffer Fools Like You]]. In this particular fallacy, rather than referring to an allegedly-expert third party, the speaker proclaims <i>him/herself</i> an expert, and insists that therefore he/she has the final say on all matters pertaining to the subject at hand (and thus wins the argument by default).",
