      "text": "\n[[Dueling Credentials]] is a fallacy for the same reason that [[Ad Verecundiam]] is a fallacy - being an expert doesn't make you right on all issues. In many fields of study, the only proper way to settle a question is through formal, verifiable research - experiments, theorems and their proofs. Conjecture, even from a Ph. D, is still that - conjecture.",
